<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22655] Fail task instead of complete task silently in PythonRunner during shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22655</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have observed in our production environment that during Spark shutdown, if there are some active tasks, sometimes they will complete with incorrect results. We&apos;ve tracked down the issue to a PythonRunner where it is returning partial result instead of throwing exception during Spark shutdown. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the better way to handle this is to have these tasks fail instead of complete with partial results (complete with partial is always bad IMHO)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
